red expectations and to embrace less constrictive modes of theorization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCaribbean literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aFeminism in literature. 0aWomen in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478012757?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478012757423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478012757/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075412-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DKUb2021